@schwarzenegger on working with Stan Lee: "He is an absolute genius." 🙌 We wholeheartedly agree!

Check out the first two episodes of the series for free, only on @kartoonchannel!: https://www.kartoonchannel.com/shows/superhero-kindergarten

“The more I realize that people are to some degree affected by what we write, the more I’m aware of the influence we have…” - Stan Lee in @rollingstone, 1971

#OnThisDay 50 years ago, the Hulk smashed his way through Rolling Stone — well, on the magazine cover, at least — instantly creating an iconic issue demonstrating Marvel’s mainstream popularity. 💥

Marvel artist Herb Trimpe drew the cover (some interior illustrations were also drawn by Marvel artists), and the accompanying six page article titled “Face front. Clap Your Hands! You’re On The Winning Team” was written by Robin Green, who replaced Flo Steinberg as Marvel’s secretary/receptionist for a brief time in the late 1960s. Robin shared stories from staffers, including Stan, and gave readers a behind the scenes glimpse at what went on in the Marvel bullpen. 

Fun fact: It would be 44 years until the Hulk landed on the cover of Rolling Stone again in May 2015!

(Be sure to look out for the Stan cameos in each episode!)

node.text:
On this day 60 years ago, history was made: The Fantastic Four, Marvel’s First Family, debuted, changing the comicbook industry – and Stan’s life – forever. 

As epic as Stan and Jack Kirby’s timeless collaboration was, Stan’s spark behind their creation is just as enduring and encouraging. If you don’t know the tale, watch this video of Stan retelling it a few years back – and if you do know it, it’s worth another listen.

#StanLee #FantasticFour #SundayMotivation

Fantastic Four 🤝 Stan Lee's Alliances 

From the space race and nuclear fears explored in The Fantastic Four six decades ago to concerns over how the digital technology we have at our fingertips can change us today in Stan Lee’s Alliances, Stan possessed an uncanny ability to tap into society’s apprehensions about our ever-evolving advances in technology and science. 

Watch Stan comment on these themes in his foreword for A Trick of Light, recorded in 2017, and catch up on the Alliances series with the newest novella, A New Reality, only on @audible at: audible.com/ANewReality 
#StanLee
